Helping others grow their businesses has always been a passion of mine. This is why I like to be as transparent as possible with my students - sharing the business side of artistry is not as popular, but it’s necessary. I built my own formula for success, so why not aid others in creating their own? 🤗 This is why I like to give business pointers along with technique based training! 

As an entrepreneur, I understand the importance of (and have benefitted from) tagging other businesses and brands. Every post won’t be perfect, but my intentions are always pure, especially if I received a paid service that I loved! We see the power of community on social media all the time, sometimes illustrated through a simple tag or shout out. And don’t worry about keeping your fave to yourself - spreading the word helps support their business and is always met with gratitude. 🥰 Let’s help each other grow our businesses!

Happy 2nd Birthday to my baby girl Brookie! 

She has grown to be such a big girl! She is so sweet and loving! Brooke is also very strong willed and I have learned to let her do her own thing which is where she thrives. Outside of her throwing her toddler fits, 😅🤦🏽‍♀️ she is a true comedian and loves making her family laugh! 

We love you! Thank you for being the missing puzzle piece to our family! Mommy 💗loves you sooooo much!

💗The day Brooke was born! I still can’t believe she is 2️⃣! 💗

Today was my first time seeing these photos and as I look through them, I realized how much my life changed after her birth! First off, 1 kid feels like 1 kid and 2 kids feels like 5! 😅 Shout out to the parents with 3 or more! Secondly, I had so many life lessons since her birth and I don’t think I would have been mentally prepared for these life lessons if it wasn’t for her birth. 

For those that don’t know, I had a water birth with Brooke! Naturally, no epidural, at home! It was the most beautiful and peaceful experience I have ever felt! I labored through the night and throughout the day. I remember hopping in my tub amazed by the water giving me immediate relief from the contractions. 😅 I was like “hmm, so that’s how that works!” 🥴 To get to my point, I’m now realizing that I must find that strength and peace in moments where I’m hurting, stressed, and uncertain and something BEAUTIFUL will come from it! 

FAQs

Did it hurt?
Surprisingly it was not bad at all. The more relaxed state I was in, it was great! It’s all in the breathing and peaceful ambiance! 

Were you nervous about having a VBAC?
No, not at all! Uterine rupture is rare, happening in less than 1% of women who have a natural labor after cesarean.

How long did you labor?
About 19 hours. I was taking naps in between and I ate for the energy! It was great! I also labored without my midwife pretty much up until we were 30 min out from the delivery.

Would you do a water birth? What are your apprehensions?

How to Love Yourself For Real 

I was reading this article from the perspective of therapists and I loved what it stated!

1.Think of self-love as a practice, not a destination—and define it for yourself.

2.Know that you don’t have to love your reality in order to love (or accept, or forgive) yourself.

3. Challenge your negative mental narrative by sticking to the facts.

4. Acknowledge that oppression and trauma can make self-love even more challenging. 

5. Practice setting boundaries—in real life and online—to build self-worth.

6. Remind yourself that loving—or at least accepting—yourself is a worthwhile pursuit.

Written By Amanda McCraken

Getting that 'makeup like skin' look is like achieving your best 'no-makeup' makeup day! It's all about enhancing your beauty while staying true to your natural self! 

I go for my tinted moisturizers or thinner foundations to achieve this look! Here I used @bobbibrown Vitamin Enriched Hydrating Skin Tint! 

Here are three simple steps to achieve a skin-like look using a skin tint:

Preparation: Start with a clean, moisturized face. Apply a lightweight primer for a smooth canvas. 
Apply Skin Tint: Use your fingers or a makeup sponge to apply a small amount of skin tint evenly across your face. Blend well to achieve a sheer, natural finish.
Set and Finish: If needed, lightly dust your T-zone with translucent powder to control shine, and finish with a setting spray for long-lasting, skin-like makeup.

These three steps will help you achieve a fresh and natural appearance with a skin tint.

Fall into the Beauty of Autumn: Achieving the Ultimate Fall Brownish Nude Lip!

 Follow these 5 steps for a stunning, gradient lip look that’s perfect for the season. 

Step 1: Define your lips with a dark brown lipliner.
Step 2: Add dimension by using a lighter brown lip liner along the edges of the darker lipliner.
Step 3: Apply a brownish nude lipstick to the center of your lips.
Step 4: Blend the lipstick into the lipliner to create a seamless gradient effect.
Step 5: Elevate your look by applying lip gloss to the center of your lips and gently feathering it into the edges.

You’re now ready to flaunt that stunning fall nude lip!

Now, let’s talk about rocking a bold red lip this season. I’ve got a good one for you! The ombré technique for red lips. It adds that extra pop and a seriously irresistible pout. All you need? Your fave red lipstick and a brown lipliner. Easy peasy, right?

I’m also on the hunt for the perfect red shade, and I’d love your input! Share your go-to red lip or any tips you have. Let’s sleigh this holiday glam together! 

Here are some quick tips to create an ombré red lip! 

1. Start Fresh:
Begin with clean, moisturized lips.

2. Outline with Brown:
Use a brown lipliner to outline the edges of your lips.

3. Base Layer:
Apply your favorite red lipstick evenly.

4. Blend Inward:
Gently blend the brown liner towards the center of your lips.

5. Smooth Transition:
Ensure a seamless transition between the red and brown.

6. Layer (If Desired):
Add more brown and red for intensity, layering as needed.

7. Clean Up:
Tidy up any edges with concealer on a small brush.

8. Set it:
Seal your ombré lip with translucent setting powder so it doesn’t get on your teeth.

9. Flaunt it:
Rock your fabulous ombré red lip with confidence!
